					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Operating systems use an interrupt to &quot;preempt&quot; an application, saving all registers and loading those of the next task. Each application has its own stack and heap, and in fact, each executes in a separate bank of RAM.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

