						<div class="postbody">Regarding the initial OS question, it's basically some sort of timer IRQ that get the CPU out of the current process, save the context of the current process and then execute some kernel code to know which process to run next (a scheduler). My description is severely over-simplified as the details get pretty complex but you get the basic picture.<br /><br />EDIT: ninja'd by tepples.</div>

					
